==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*malan-'', from Indo-European ''*melh₂-'' ‘grind’.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[mel]], Old Saxon [[melo]] (Dutch [[meel]]), Old High German [[melo]] (German [[Mehl]]), Old Norse [[mjǫl]] (Swedish [[mjöl]]).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Hittite ''malla-'', Greek [[μύλη]], Latin [[molere]], Old Church Slavonic [[мелѭ]] (Russian [[мелю]]), Lithuanian [[malti|málti]], Old Irish [[melim]] (Breton [[malaf]]), Tocharian A ''mläs-''.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'melʊ/

===Noun===
'''melu''' ''n''
# [[meal]], the edible part of a grain or pulse

